<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870115-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Jacobs Engineering GroupNames Watson President</HL><DD> 01/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS JEC </IN><DATELINE> PASADENA, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Noel G. Watson, executive vice president, was named president and chief operating officer of Jacobs Engineering Group Inc., an engineering, design and construction concern.    As president, he succeeds Joseph J. Jacobs who will continue as chairman and chief executive officer. The job of chief operating officer is a new position.    The company also elected two new directors: J. Clayburn LaForce, dean of the graduate school of management at the University of California at Los Angeles, and David M. Petrone, vice chairman of Wells Fargo Bank, San Francisco.    The new directors succeed Dale Myers, who resigned recently after being named deputy administrator of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration and Gary L. Allison, who resigned the posts of director and executive vice president to pursue other interests. Mr. Allison will continue as a consultant at the company. </TEXT></DOC>